    "Factories' shop floors accommodate electronic devices like computers and digital sensors to drive production.",
    "Programmable logic controllers (PLCs) and manufacturing robots were two significant additions to industrial production processes.",
    "Integrating computers, telecommunications practices, and electronic components led to a rise in human brain qualities in production processes-the interconnected components aimed to bring more intelligence into factories, increasing \"automation\" for industrial operations.",
    "Factory operators' working conditions considerably progressed during this revolution compared to the previous one.",
    "However, the world started to experience repercussions like environmental pollution and degradation, overurbanization, and labor exploitation of workers."
